AFRICA
Dong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-American artist, travels the world sketching and painting
the beautiful, the monumental and the picturesque. His watercolors grace more than forty
permanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad.
Africa is a continent of great natural beauty. In addition to abundant wild game it contains a
mixture of mountains, jungles, magnificent rivers, open plains, and arid deserts.
Many of its cities are bustling metropolises with broad avenues, modern buildings,
good restaurants and fine hotels, including several Inter • Continental Hotels.
From New York, Pan Am 747's serve Dakar, Monrovia, Accra, Lagos, Abidjan, and Nairobi
Mr. Kingman's painting depicts majestic, snowcapped Mount Kilamanjaro in Tanzania.
At 19,340 feet it is Africa's highest mountain.
@PAN AM
